problem_text: If the restaurant is listed in Yelp’s recommendations, then the restaurant does not receive many negative reviews. All restaurants with a rating greater than 9 are listed in Yelp’s recommendations. Some restaurants that do not provide take-out service receive many negative reviews. All restaurants that are popular among local residents have ratings greater than 9. Subway has a rating greater than 9 or is popular among local residents.
predicates:
ListedInYelp(x) ::: x is listed in Yelp’s recommendations.
ManyNegativeReviews(x) ::: x receives many negative reviews.
RatingGreaterThan9(x) ::: x has a rating greater than 9.
YelpRecommendations(x) ::: x is a Yelp recommendation.
TakeOut(x) ::: x provides take-out service.
PopularLocal(x) ::: x is popular among local residents.
Restaurant(x) ::: x is a restaurant.
Subway ::: Subway.

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Subway is popular among local residents and provides take-out service, then Subway is not listed in Yelp’s recommendations.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Subway is not popular among local residents, then Subway does not have a rating greater than 9.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Subway is not popular among local residents, then Subway does not provide take-out service.
tests.conclusions: PopularLocal(subway) ⊕ RatingGreaterThan9(subway) ::: Subway has a rating greater than 9 or is popular among local residents. FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Subway does not provide take-out service, then Subway does not receive many negative reviews.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Subway is listed in Yelp’s recommendations, then Subway is not popular among local residents.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Subway is a restaurant and popular among local residents, then Subway is listed in Yelp’s recommendations.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Subway is a restaurant and does not provide take-out service.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Subway is popular among local residents, then Subway is listed in Yelp’s recommendations.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Subway is a restaurant and does not receive many negative reviews, then Subway provides take-out service.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If Subway is a restaurant that is listed in Yelp’s recommendations, then Subway provides take-out service.
